'''Wilson''' is a  in , , .  The population was 5,840 at the 2000 census.  The town is said to be named after an early settler. 
The '''Town of Wilson'''  is on the northern border of the county and contains a village, also called .  
The Town of Wilson was established in 1818.  The origin of the town name is supposedly Reuben Wilson.
According to the , the town has a total area of 51.5&nbsp;s (133.3&nbsp;), of which, 49.5&nbsp;square miles (128.3&nbsp;km²) of it is land and 1.9&nbsp;square miles (5.0&nbsp;km²) of it (3.75%) is water. 
The Town of Wilson is on the south shore of .
North-south highway  (Wilson-Cambria Road) intersects  (Seaway Trail) in Wilson village.
As of the {{GR|2}} of 2000, there were 5,840 people, 2,224 households, and 1,672 families residing in the town.  The  was 117.9 people per square mile (45.5/km²).  There were 2,438 housing units at an average density of 49.2/sq&nbsp;mi (19.0/km²).  The racial makeup of the town was 97.57% , 0.38%  or , 0.53% , 0.26% , 0.03% , 0.36% from , and 0.87% from two or more races.  or  of any race were 0.84% of the population. Also, Wilson features a growing gay population.
This has become well known after a homosexual hazing incident on a bus.
There were 2,224 households out of which 33.9% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 62.4% were  living together, 7.8% had a female householder with no husband present, and 24.8% were non-families. 21.1% of all households were made up of individuals and 9.9% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 2.63 and the average family size was 3.04.
In the town the population was spread out with 25.7% under the age of 18, 6.3% from 18 to 24, 28.1% from 25 to 44, 26.4% from 45 to 64, and 13.5% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 39 years. For every 100 females there were 97.4 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 96.4 males.
The median income for a household in the town was $44,557, and the median income for a family was $47,180. Males had a median income of $40,750 versus $23,494 for females. The  for the town was $19,654.  About 3.4% of families and 5.2% of the population were below the , including 5.3% of those under age 18 and 3.4% of those age 65 or over.
